    "description": "<p id=\"isPasted\">👣 Follow These Steps 👣</p><p><br></p><p>⚡&nbsp;Trigger&nbsp;⚡</p><ol start=\"1\" style='box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(55, 65, 81); font-family: \"Inter var\", helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);' type=\"1\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"></li></ol><p>🔨 Inspire SOPs 🔨</p><p id=\"isPasted\">Site Measure is essential to getting the design accurate which results in a smooth install!</p><ol><li>Review Job</li><li>Confirm Site address</li><li>Locate Site Measure plan in the Job files (Files &gt; Manufacturing &gt; Site Measure)&nbsp;</li><li>Take this with you to site (preferably electronic)</li><li>Complete site measure, requirements are:<ul><li>Wall Length&nbsp;</li><li>Wall Height&nbsp;</li><li>Window dimensions&nbsp;</li><li>Window elevation and distance to adjacent walls</li><li>Plumbing centres</li><li>Bulkhead location and dimensions&nbsp;</li><li>Note any anomalies that may affect the install or manufacturing of the kitchen.</li></ul></li><li>All measurements on plan need to be checked and confirmed:<ul><li>if correct Circle the measurement&nbsp;</li><li>if incorrect, draw a strike through the measurement and write the correct measurement next to it.</li></ul></li><li>Once completed, save a copy as \"Site Measure - Completed\":<ol><li>Electronic- ensure file is saved in Jobman files&nbsp;</li><li>Printed - upload a photo of the printed copy to Jobman files</li></ol></li></ol><p>⏰ Expected Timelines ⏰</p><p>Site measure should be scheduled 5 days prior to task due date.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p>",
