    "description": "<p id=\"isPasted\">👣 Follow These Steps 👣</p><p><br></p><p>⚡&nbsp;Trigger&nbsp;⚡</p><ol start=\"1\" style='box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(55, 65, 81); font-family: \"Inter var\", helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);' type=\"1\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><br></li></ol><p>🔨 Inspire SOPs 🔨</p><p>Site measure has been completed and is ready for the design review in preparation for BOM finalisation. Please:</p><ol style='box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(55, 65, 81); font-family: \"Inter var\", helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;'><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Swap the generic wall unit to a rangehood cabinet (this has cutout for spec of rangehood and ducting space)</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Swap the generic wall under panel to a rangehood under panel (this has cutout for spec of rangehood)</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Adjust drawing as per site measure shorten/length wall as necessary and therefore adjust cabinetry accordingly</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Delete the 40mm ceiling scribes and input CSP 120 (found in tall panels 18mm)</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Delete the toe skins in molding tab and add in 2400W toe kicks (amount required to cover front feet area) - Always round up</li><li>Generate and save Multiprints copies in the <strong>Job</strong> and <strong>Workorder&nbsp;</strong>\"Shared\" folders, as follows:&nbsp;<ul><li>Technical Drawings (plans + elevations)&nbsp;</li><li>Tops Plan &nbsp;</li><li>Renders&nbsp;</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Archive any previous designs plans in the Jobman Files Shared folder so that only the updated version is in there.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Navigate to the materials section of the Workorder and review the Mozaik BOM alongside the Jobman BOM.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Update the Jobman BOM to reflect the same materials and quantities detailed in the Mozaik BOM.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Review Loom video \"Source materials\"</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Click Source&nbsp;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><strong>Deselect&nbsp;</strong>\"Source Stock in Transit\"&nbsp;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Click Source in the pop-up window.&nbsp;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Complete this task.</li></ol><p>⏰ Expected Timelines ⏰</p><p id=\"isPasted\"><br></p>",
