  {
    "id": "45b05e7b-d394-4765-aa5b-dbe94535c2f4",
    "name": "🪚 Cut",
    "step_id": "a6b1bfe1-fc3c-4259-b0bb-b4f0c68fdd39",
    "description": "<p id=\"isPasted\">👣 Follow These Steps 👣</p><p>🔨 Inspire SOPs 🔨</p><p>While the CNC is largely automated it still requires a skilled operator to ensure a successful cut.&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Check tooling is appropriate and in good condition.</li><li>Ensure all aspects of CNC are clean and free of debris or excessive dust.</li><li>Pick board from store rack with appropriate Job Number&nbsp;</li><li id=\"isPasted\">Navigate to the jobs files and review:<ul><li>BOM&nbsp;</li><li>Patterns&nbsp;</li></ul></li><li>Confirm the right board colour/finish and quantity are on the loading bed for cutting.</li><li>Review G-Code file and load onto USB&nbsp;</li><li>Load USB into CNC tower.&nbsp;</li><li>Select appropriate settings and begin CNC of board.</li><li>While cutting review the patterns and what is being cut to ensure they're in alignment.</li><li>Tick off each sheet on pattern doc as completed. (electronic)&nbsp;</li><li>Once sheet is completed stay clear of CNC bed until offloading is complete.</li><li>Once Offloading complete load into trolley for Edge Banding.&nbsp;</li></ol><p><em>NOTE: if there are miscuts or damages note this with an X on the patterns and regenerate the g-code file for that item and recut at end of job.</em></p><p>⏰ Expected Timelines ⏰</p><p>Once all materials are availble</p>",
    "organisation_id": "fbc41182-dffc-4597-ab02-462388d6a239",
