  {
    "id": "78df2215-31f6-4019-98d1-a734e287c05c",
    "name": "📼 Edge Banding",
    "step_id": "a6b1bfe1-fc3c-4259-b0bb-b4f0c68fdd39",
    "description": "<p>👣 Follow These Steps 👣</p><p><br></p><p>⚡&nbsp;Trigger&nbsp;⚡</p><ol start=\"1\" style='box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(55, 65, 81); font-family: \"Inter var\", helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);' type=\"1\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"></li></ol><p>🔨 Inspire SOPs 🔨</p><p>Follow these Steps:</p><ol style='box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(55, 65, 81); font-family: \"Inter var\", helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Review the following located in the Job Files:&nbsp;<ul><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">BOM&nbsp;</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Infosheet&nbsp;</li></ul></li><li>Inspect cut panels for damage and odd shapes.</li><li>Take any panels that require hand edging to Assembly area and detail what the edging requirements are.&nbsp;</li><li>Ensure Edging assignments are correct (PVC or Laser) and make sense.&nbsp;</li><li>Check Edge tape assigned vs board colour and ensure the match or contrast as expected.</li><li>Set up Edging machine for the correct edging assignment.&nbsp;</li><li>Ensure the machine is clean and free of excess glue or debris.</li><li>Complete Edging checking each piece to ensure the edging is of good quality.&nbsp;</li><li>Once edged completely place into trolley.&nbsp;</li></ol><p><em>NOTE: If using PVC UG tape, White glue for white/light colours and Black glue for Black/Dark colours&nbsp;</em></p><p><em>NOTE: When panels have elements that require hand edging these must be taken straight to the assembly team for completion. Once completed the panel must be brought back to the Edge Banding station for inspection and to go on the trolley. &nbsp;</em></p><p>⏰ Expected Timelines ⏰</p><p>As materials are available&nbsp;</p>",
    "organisation_id": "fbc41182-dffc-4597-ab02-462388d6a239",
