  {
    "id": "b243e454-b755-4876-840f-240a05d08af0",
    "name": "🔬 Checking and Wrapping",
    "step_id": "0b96ad76-73f7-42c7-a4fa-a8179179f12d",
    "description": "<p id=\"isPasted\">👣 Follow These Steps 👣</p><p><br></p><p>⚡&nbsp;Trigger&nbsp;⚡</p><ol start=\"1\" style='box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(55, 65, 81); font-family: \"Inter var\", helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);' type=\"1\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"></li></ol><p>🔨 Inspire SOPs 🔨</p><p>QA checks are essential for a quality product</p><ol><li>Inspect each panel for the following:<ul><li>Chips, Cracks, Scratches in Melamine.</li><li>Defects in board surface.&nbsp;</li><li>Incorrect edging.</li><li>Damaged edging.&nbsp;</li></ul></li><li>If damage can be remedied do so, if a recut/edge is required notify the factory manager.&nbsp;</li><li>Wipe down panels as you go with a dry rag or spray and wipe for more stubborn marks.</li><li>Wrap panels for cabinets in their elements, Ensure the stickers are reviewed to avoid mixing elements up.&nbsp;</li><li>Ensure all cabinet pieces are present before completing.</li><li>Put items back into trolley.&nbsp;</li></ol><p>⏰ Expected Timelines ⏰</p><p>Within 24 hours of Cut and Edge&nbsp;</p>",
